  <text>
    <body>
      <head>Ogre Battle</head>
      <p>
        <l>Now once upon a time - an old man told me a fable</l>
        <l>When the piper is gone - and the soup is cold on your table</l>
        <l>And if the black crow flies to find a new destination - that is the sign</l>
        <l>Come tonight</l>
        <l>Come to the ogre sight</l>
        <l>Come to the ogre-battle-fight</l>
      </p>
      <p>
        <l>He gives a great big cry and he can swallow up the ocean</l>
        <l>With a mighty tongue he catches flies - the palm of his hand is incredible</l>
        <l>One great big eye - has a focus in your direction</l>
        <l>Now the battle is on</l>
        <l>Yeah yeah yeah</l>
        <l>Come tonight</l>
        <l>Come to the ogre sight</l>
        <l>Come to the ogre-battle-fight</l>
      </p>
      <p>
        <l>The ogre men are still inside</l>
        <l>The two-way mirror mountain</l>
        <l>Gotta keep down right out of sight</l>
        <l>You can't see in but they can see out</l>
        <l>&quot;Keep a look out&quot;</l>
        <l>The ogre-men are coming out</l>
        <l>From the two-way mirror mountain</l>
        <l>They're running up behind you and they're coming all about</l>
        <l>Can't go east 'cos you gotta go south</l>
      </p>
      <p>
        <l>Ogre-men are going home</l>
        <l>And the great big fight is over</l>
        <l>Bugle blow, the trumpet cry</l>
        <l>Ogre battle lives for ever more</l>
        <l>You can come along</l>
        <l>You can come along</l>
        <l>Come to ogre battle</l>
      </p>
    </body>
